{"/service/ndnp/ct/batch_ct_animals_ver01/data/sn92051501/00271763724/1908011501/0236.xml":{"full_text":"THE PRESS, STAFFORD SPRINGS, CONN., WEDNESDAY, JANUARY 15, 1908.\n1\nHISTORICAL EVENTS\n1808-1812\n180S Election of James Madison\nPresident of the IT. S. Birth of\nGeneral Robert E. Lee(d. 1870).\n09 Birth of Abraham Lincoln (d.\n186.-,) Birth of Dr. Oliver Wendell\nHolmes (d. 1894) A strike of New\nYork bootmakers.\nIO The census showed that the pop?\nulation of the seventeen States was\nabout seven and a quarter millions\nDubuque, Iowa, settled by the\nFrench.\n'II War in the V. S, commenced\nagainst the Indian chief Tecumseh\nand his league The American Fur\nCo. built Fort Astoria, Oregon.\n'12 Declaration of war by the United\nStates against Great Britain Na\nval victories by the U. S. frigates\nConstitution' and United States\nAdmission of the State of Louisi\nana to the American Union.\n1843-1847\n1843 Rhodelsland adopts new Con\nstitution Present system of cadet\nappointment to West Point adopt\ned Ironinaker strike at Pitts\nburg. 44 Copper was discovered at Lake\nSuperior Morse telegraph com\npleted and the first telegram sent\nfrom Washington to Baltimore.\n'45 Brigham Young became head\nof Mormons and moved West\nFlorida admitted to the Union\nt'nitfd States Naval Academy\nopened War was commented with\nMexico I eath of Andrew Jack\nson. '46- Iowa admitted to the Union\nElias Howe patents the sewing\nmachine.\n47 Hoe patents the cylinder print\ning press Conquest of New Mex\nico ami California San Francisco\nwas named Postage stamps first\nissued.\n1848-1852\n1848 Mormons found Salt Lake\nCity, Utah Death of John Quincy\nAdams Peace was declared be\ntween U. S. and Mexico Gold was\ndiscovered in California Wiscon\nsin admitted to the Union.\n'49 Inauguration of Taylor and Fill\nmore Strike at Pittsburg Treaty\nsitrned between U. S. and Hawaii.\n'50 Trouble in Congress over Cali\nfornia and the slavery question\nCalifornia admitted, to the Union\nDeath